<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1267101-how-does-this-book-get-a-3-8-star-rating">How does this book get a 3.8 star rating when it won&#39;t be released for a few months?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1267101'><a id="like_count_community_question_1267101" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1267101?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">26 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F36124936-the-outsider">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1267101-how-does-this-book-get-a-3-8-star-rating">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1267101-how-does-this-book-get-a-3-8-star-rating">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/42977481-jennifer"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1577939630i/42977481._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/42977481-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">As someone else already said people can receive ARC&apos;s however because Goodreads allows reviews before release, people tend to rate the book regardless<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">As someone else already said people can receive ARC's however because Goodreads allows reviews before release, people tend to rate the book regardless of whether or not they have read it. For Example, some will rate it 5 stars simply because they love Stephen King and write "IM SO EXCITED FOR THIS" as a review. It's really unfortunate.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

